XRD was used to investigate the crystalline structure present in the respective samples. Representative GO and RGO powder samples are presented in Fig. 3. A typical GO XRD pattern is presented in Fig. 3a and displays the characteristic diffraction peak located at 2θ = 11.66°, which was attributed to the (001) crystalline plane of GO. The corresponding inter-layer spacing (d spacing) of powder samples were calculated using Eq. (1) below:1dspace=λ2sinθ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
